<br>
I was wondering a few things - I am at lvl 51, making work of getting to Run speed 3 asap.<br>
<br>
I've gone about 1yellow/1blue bub into the level, since dying only seems to take away some of yer regular exp, none of the AA exp. - I like a safe margin.<br>
<br>
I've tried setting AAXP and reg XP to 50/50 at first, but it seems that AA-exp advances more rapidly then regular exp does, or is this my imagintion?<br>
<br>
A friend told me that AAXP at lvl 51 advances at the rate of somewhere in the 40's - is this correct, and if so - what level exactly?<br>
<br>
Thanks for any answers....<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yanaripethugger>Yanari Pethugger</A> at: 11/21/02 8:19:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=umar666>Umar666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/25/02 2:08:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=109.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions on AA experience</span><hr size=1> don't know for sure, but I did run one &quot;controlled experiment&quot; over the summer.<br>
<br>
I went through all of 56th (one one of my chars in another realm) with AA split 50/50 with normal exp.  I got my third AA (all in 56th) within like 3 kills of dinging 57th.<br>
<br>
That is about as anal as I get with knowing the internals of the game nowadays...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.csds.uidaho.edu/~dont/marquis.html">Marquis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, 49th Mage of Ebon Storm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaranna>Jaranna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/25/02 8:07:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=109.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions on AA experience</span><hr size=1> One AA point is equal to a halfling druid going through level 52.  AA is the same for everyone.<br>
<br>
At least, this is what I am told repeatedly by those who know more about it than I do.  I personally take their word for it, as I really don't have the patience or understanding to really test it.  All I know is that as a 52 human wizard, I get AAs faster than levels.  I've got Run3 and am currently 100% normal XP until I get ready to ding 53, then it's full AA for regen.<br>
<br>
This is my first character, and I want to make sure to kill the old world dragons before I move on. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/thewok/jaranna.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
