<br>
I am 1 yellow and 1 blue bubble in lvl 51 - is this a safe margin?  What is the max. exp you can lose from dying?  <br>
I once lost like 3 blue bubbles, that was most I ever lost - but can you lose more from 1 kill (i.e. - am I safe enough in my level?)<br>
<br>
The second question - say you need as much exp for 1 lvl AA as you need to go through lvl 51 in regular EXP - if I were to hit lvl 52, would I then still need just the exp I needed at lvl 51 for AA, or will this increase? <br>
<br>
(theoretical example : I kill seafurbies at lvl 51 now for AA exp and get 1blue stripe per kill on average - so 125 seafurbies dead would get me my AA-lvl.  <br>
If I were to lvl to 52, and then just go for AA-exp again, will 125 seafurbies still suffice, or will they give less exp in AA because I am higher level?)<br>
<br>
I know these aren't easy questions - but I would love to get my new pet heal (lvl 52 spell) and then continue to AA-exp but I don't wanna do so at a higher kill-cost for the same exp-levels I get now in AA.<br>
<br>
Thanks for any and all answers...<br>
<br>
Yanari Pethugger,<br>
